                    <h3>What is DOMContentLoaded?</h3>
                    <p>The DOMContentLoaded event fires when the initial HTML document has been completely loaded and parsed, without waiting for stylesheets, images, and subframes to finish loading.</p>
                    
                    <h3>Why is it important?</h3>
                    <p>This metric is crucial because it measures when your page's content is available for user interaction. A lower time means users can start using your site faster.</p>
                </div>
